fields.description: The constraint is that the Zerg player is forbidden to make any Queens.
fields.name: No Queens!

fields.description: Players may not expand until they have a carrier.
fields.name: Carrier Rush

fields.description: The constraint this week is to play with no Marines, Marauders, or Tanks
fields.name: No Marines, Marauders, or Tanks!

fields.description: Players must kill their opponents in alphabetical order in Free For All matches.
fields.name: Alphabetical Free For All

fields.description: Players must pick the same race and may not make the same Units all game long!
fields.name: Halfsies!

fields.description: The constraint: the player must expand every 4 to 5 minutes.
fields.name: Expo Hungry

fields.description: Players are given the following constraint: The player must attack your opponent(s) every 5 minutes and whenever you attack, you must emit a battle cry!
fields.name: 5 Minute Attacks!

fields.description: Players are given the following constraint: Build a Battlecruiser before expanding.
fields.name: Battlecruisers!

fields.description: Players must attack only through the use of Nydus Worms
fields.name: Nydus Crazy

fields.description: The constraint: Players can only attack using Warp Prism harassment until they have at least 3 bases.
fields.name: Warp Prisms

fields.description: Players may expand anywhere BUT they cannot take their natural expansion. Ever.
fields.name: What Natural Expansion?

fields.description: The constraint: Players are asked to build Queens constantly throughout the game!
fields.name: Mass Queen!

fields.description: Use contamination as much as possible!
fields.name: Contaminate This!

fields.description: The constraint: One Fish Two Fish Red Fish NUKEFISH! Build a nuke before expanding and talk like Dr. Seuss before launching a nuke.
fields.name: Nukes and Suess

fields.description: Protoss players may only build 2 Warp Gates
fields.name: 2 Gate Challenge

fields.description: At the beginning of your game, you must name three Units. For the rest of the game, you may only make those three Units (and workers/buildings, of course).
fields.name: Count to Three

fields.description: No Roaches, no Hydras, no Mutas, no Banelings - only 12 Zerglings all game! Fun Zerg play focused on late game tech & Units ensues.
fields.name: Zerg Tier Tears

fields.description: Terran players may only have 1 Barracks and 1 Factory working, the rest must be Starports.
fields.name: StarportCraft

fields.description: Name a unit and introduce it, then get as many kills as possible with it.
fields.name: Hero Has Arrived

fields.description: Play with only your mouse!
fields.name: No Keyboard, No Problem

fields.description: Protoss players may not build any pylons in their base.
fields.name: Not a Pylon in Sight

fields.description: Players may only attack on creep.
fields.name: Attack on Creep

fields.description: Terran players must take their command center and planetary fortress rush!
fields.name: Planetary Fortress Rushing

fields.description: Terran players must move their command center to another base before playing the game like normal.
fields.name: We Have Liftoff

fields.description: 2v2 where one player can only build ground units and the other can only build air units!
fields.name: One if by Land, Two if by Sea

fields.description: Players are challenged to make do with only queens, spines, spores, Overlords, Overseers, Drones, and no other units.
fields.name: Unitless Zerg Play

fields.description: Protoss players are not allowed to make stalkers.
fields.name: No Stalkers!

fields.description: Players have to expand 3 times before doing anything substantial.
fields.name: 4 gate? Try 4 Base!

fields.description: 2v2 where after the 5 minute mark one player may only build units and one player may only expand.
fields.name: 2v2 Money Dump

fields.description: Protoss players may only cannon rush!
fields.name: Cannon Rush!

fields.description: Players are not allowed to expand on their half of the map.
fields.name: The Wrong Side of the Bed

fields.description: All players must have a 50% handicap
fields.name: Half Health Battles

fields.description: Players are not allowed to expand until they have begun building a mothership.
fields.name: Mothership Rush

fields.description: 4v4 where the team declares one of their teammates as the 'Champion'. The Champion may only have 20 supply of workers and the rest of the team can only have 20 supply of army.
fields.name: Champion

fields.description: Free For All. Players declare a single unit they are going to build, they cannot build others. Once a player has left, the players may pick another unit that they will build, etc etc.
fields.name: 1-2-3 For All

fields.description: Players must ask their opponent to choose two Units (that don't start with the same letter and aren't workers) that the player will be prohibited from using
fields.name: 2 Units Gone

fields.description: Players must bring all workers except for 10 in every engagement.
fields.name: Kamakaze!

fields.description: Zerg players must bring a spine crawler with every attack.
fields.name: Defense is OFFENSE!

fields.description: Zerg players must do as much damage as possible with burrowed banelings.
fields.name: Burrowed Banelings!

fields.description: Players can only defend and counter attack.
fields.name: Counterattack Only

fields.description: All of vital structures must be powered by one Pylon, and that Pylon must not be in your base!
fields.name: Artosis Pylownage

fields.description: Cannons must be the backbone of your army.
fields.name: Cannon Pushing!

fields.description: You can build only air units.
fields.name: Only Air!

fields.description: Player must mind control an opponent's worker and build units of that race, then kill their opponent with their own race.
fields.name: Stop Hitting Yourself!

fields.description: You may ONLY attack worker lines! Sure you can defend if you so desire, but you are absolutely disallowed from engaging the enemy army mid-map! KILL THEM WORKERS!
fields.name: Only Attack Worker Lines

fields.description: Terran may only attack with nukes.
fields.name: Nuke to Win

fields.description: Using as little number of units as possible kill your opponent.
fields.name: Kill your opponent with few units
